    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-18T06:26:21+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-18T06:26:21+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T20:56:21Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-17T20:56:21Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system south of the Bight extends a ridge over SA. The high will slowly move east over the weekend ahead of a cold front which will slip to the south of SA and weaken. The high will remain near stationary in the southern Tasman Sea, maintaining a ridge across the state early next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. The chance of a thunderstorm in the far west during this afternoon and evening. Winds northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending northwest to northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h in the early morning. Daytime maximum temperatures 30 to 36.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:40am to 3:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower south of Woomera in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Coober Pedy in the morning. Winds northwest to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending northeast to southeasterly in the early afternoon then tending south to southeasterly in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 15 and 18 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-21T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-19T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-20T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds northeast to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 12 and 16 with daytime temperatures reaching 28 to 34.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-21T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-22T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-20T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-21T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny day. The chance of a thunderstorm in the far west in the evening. Winds north to northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 14 and 21 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 30s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
